<br>
I had the harness of control and ported to GD each time I logged on and lo and behold about 4 days of trying she was up!<br>
<br>
But she was the PET of an ELITE FROST GIANT.<br>
<br>
Damn buggy quest.<br>
<br>
Assembled a little group (60 rouge, 52 nec, and me 50 Druid)  Attacked the giant (fully expecting the BM to act as a normal pet) but the BM seemed to be ATTACHED to the Giant.  It would attack us, but when I rooted the Giant the Broodmother just stood there beside him.<br>
<br>
We just root/dotted the giant then had the GM that I /petitioned clear the aggro on the BM. (Yes, the GM agreed that it was bugged, but wouldn't help us kill the giant.)<br>
<br>
So if this happens to you, kill the giant.. zone to clear aggro and the Broodmother will return to normal.<br>
<br>
P.S. I handed in the harness while she was wandering... took a LONG while but eventually she went to fort and we snagged Fergul.<br>
<br>
Have a nice day<br>
<br>
